{
  "texts": [
    "For a class to be tested, the proposed approach (called CAME) extracts the latest n versions of this class, and for each version, it extracts the selected code metrics (e.g., the complexity of the class).",
    "As a result, it expresses the evolution of the class as a matrix X n,m where n is the number of versions and m is the number of involved code metrics.",
    "This matrix is fed into a CNN whose output is forwarded to an MLP (multilayer perceptron).",
    "The MLP will make the final prediction, i.e., whether the class under test is a God class.",
    "Notably, although this approach depends on deep neural networks, it leverages only 71 real-world God classes for training and testing.Yu et al. [223] employed a GNN to detect feature-envy smells."
  ]
}